des:
If you have any problem when you use this skill, you can contact us by email: service@avatarcontrols.com

AvatarControls skill for Amazon Alexa to help you control home appliances nicely and easily.
You can simply ask Alexa to turn on, turn off or dim the light. 
There’s no need to go to the switch to adjust your home light - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo, Echo Dot, Amazon Tap, or Echo Show. 

After connecting Alexa to your AvatarControls products in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our "AvatarControls" app in the android or ios app market;
(2). Register one AvatarControls account in our "AvatarControls" app;
(3). You need to have some AvatarControls devices in hand;
(4). Configure these devices in our “AvatarControls" app and change the appropriate name for your devices which will be used in "AvatarControls" skills;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android, ios or Amazon app market;
(6). Configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(7). Search "AvatarControls" skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of "AvatarControls", and you'll be navigated to AvatarControls login page;
(9). Input your AvatarControls account username and password, you'll be redirected to the success page;
(10). Now all setup is finished. 

You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa, turn on kitchen light"
“Alexa, turn off kitchen light"
“Alexa, dim livingroom light"
“Alexa, brighten livingroom light"
“Alexa, set the livingroom light to 20 percent"
“Alexa, set bedroom light to Blue"

Currently, this skill supports products:
smart switch,
smart socket, 
smart ceiling fans,
smart ceiling lamp,
smart strip light,
smart string light,
smart bulbs...
